<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="20" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,258,1693]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,1488,1513]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Comments.</emphasis>
Although this species is known from a large collection of about 
<specimenCount box="[1071,1238,1488,1513]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" type="generic">
<number box="[1071,1113,1488,1512]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" value="300.0">300</number>
specimens
</specimenCount>
taken during one week in 
<number box="[253,312,1525,1549]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" value="1984.0">1984</number>
, it is unknown from any other collections. A second winged species was taken in much smaller numbers at the same time. That other species, 
<taxonomicName box="[676,846,1560,1584]" class="Insecta" family="Sphaeroceridae" genus="Howickia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lepidostylus">
<emphasis box="[676,846,1560,1584]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">H. lepidostylus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, is easily distinguished by the abdominal characters given in the key but is externally identical to 
<taxonomicName box="[668,776,1596,1620]" class="Insecta" family="Sphaeroceridae" genus="Howickia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oliveri">
<emphasis box="[668,776,1596,1620]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">H. oliveri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Females of these two species were associated by relative abundance (the rare females were assumed to be associated with the rare male and were both treated as 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Sphaeroceridae" genus="Howickia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lepidostylus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">H. lepidostylus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). No females were treated as 
<typeStatus box="[618,666,1669,1693]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">type</typeStatus>
specimens.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
